dataStructure.name: sid.org.tmforum.tip.resource.res.log.itf.SerialInterface
dataStructure.description:
This is a concrete class that refines the concept of a DeviceInterface into a SerialDeviceInterface.

This entity is optional
dataStructure.label: SerialInterface

child.name: bandwidth
child.description:
This defines the bandwidth of this interface.

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional
child.label: bandwidth

child.name: clockRate
child.description:
This defines the clock rate of a DCE device. If this is a DTE device, then this attribute should be NULL.

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional
child.label: clockRate

child.name: isDCE
child.description:
This is a Boolean attribute that, if TRUE, defines this as a DCE device (i.e., one that supplies a clocking signal). If the value of this attribute is FALSE, then it is a DTE device (one that uses clocking).

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional
child.label: isDCE
